# Writing Style for External Communication

When drafting GitLab MR replies, Slack messages, or any communication that will appear as if written by the user, follow these guidelines.

## Tone

- Casual and direct. No corporate-speak, no filler.
- Lowercase at the start of sentences is fine and preferred. Don't capitalize unless it's a proper noun or acronym.
- Short sentences. Get to the point fast.
- Confident but not arrogant. State what was done, not why you're amazing.
- Technical without being showy. Use the actual function/variable names when relevant.

## Structure

- Lead with acknowledgment if responding to feedback ("good catch", "you're right", "yeah that was broken").
- Then state what was done to fix it, briefly.
- Add just enough technical detail so a reviewer can verify without re-reading the diff.
- No bullet points or headers in MR comments unless the reply is genuinely long.
- One paragraph is usually enough. Two max.

## Avoid

- Hyphens and em-dashes. Use commas or periods instead.
- Exclamation marks (almost never).
- Emojis.
- Phrases like "Great suggestion!", "Thanks for catching this!", "I've gone ahead and..."
- Starting replies with "Hey" or "Hi".
- Overly formal transitions ("Additionally", "Furthermore", "As a result").
- Summarizing back what the reviewer said before responding.

## Examples

Good: "good catch, just pushed a fix for this. wired up ActivitySession data so lastEngagedAt is actually populated now."

Good: "fixed, was using the wrong ID field for the lookup. switched to caseVehicleId and it resolves correctly now."

Good: "you are reading it right, the other tabs are unaffected. just pushed a commit that addresses both comments."

Bad: "Great catch! I've gone ahead and addressed this by wiring up the ActivitySession data — this should now correctly populate the `lastEngagedAt` field. Let me know if you have any other concerns!"

Bad: "Thanks for the thorough review, Jonathon. I appreciate you flagging this. Here's what I've done to address your feedback..."

# Linear Ticket Context

- **Team**: ClaimView (Derpy) (ID: `dee44e1e-3888-4e50-ab31-cdea658bf18e`)
- **Ticket prefix**: CV (e.g., CV-1234)

When creating or referencing Linear tickets, use the ClaimView (Derpy) team by default.
